title: LCLS II FACET II Installation Activities
text: Friday, 1/14/2022 40 people badged in at the morning tailgate. Progress: ACCPHYS - Spreader component checkout. AMRF - SSA p/m. CM cable connections. LLRF checkout. ARDTF - FACET II support. CBL - RF/BCS support. S8, cable installation. S20, FACET II cable installation. S30, cable tagging. S0-S10, conduit fire putty installation. CTLS - Motion control system checkout. Tunnel radio signal checkout. Profile monitor checkout. MPS, link node checkout. FACOI - S1, air panel prv replacement. FACOM - LCW system p/m. Prep for S11 KCS pump replacement. Metrology - OTR0H04 alignment. MFD - Linac East vacuum activities. (Sat) S28-S30, magnet water connections. Housing housekeeping. (Sat) Component base grouting and form installation. (Sat) He guard line installation. OTR0H04 installation. Injector, downstream vent and removal of pump COL0:762 for repair PEM - LCLS and FACET II support. S4, magnet connections. S1-S4, magnet labeling. S1,mcor crate loto. Diag kicker checkout. S28,S29, magnet checkout. PPS - Prep for LCLS start-up. S0-S10 testing. (Sun) Test Lab - NIRP system labeling. Penetration shielding labeling. Contractors - Collins - S28-S30, component base grouting. Vance Brown - S0 fire station project. Regards, Al

text: "01/14/22 22:30 - Jesse Peralta - C1 - HRS..-HRS. SCWS 1) Worked on Layout for adding Isolation valves to Hot side of Plate & Frame HTX on secondary water loop filter skid - Located 2 - 2" Jamesburry Valves - Staged the Box wrench and socket wrench for separation of HTX plates (1 5/8") - marked 2" SS pipe for cut and modifying the inlet and outlet of Hot side of HTX 2) Research cleaning solutions for flushing and cleaning of HTX in place and if separated" 01/14/22 18:10 - Mike Stivala - C2 - HRS.CS.CW-C2-FL21460 (C2-CMP214 H2O flow gauge) observed to have gathered condensation on inside of lens and reading incorrectly. Gauge may be defective or damaged. 01/14/22 18:00 - Mike Stivala - C0 (common) - HRS.AX.RC-Recovery compressor controls (for both compressors) reset in order to energize oil sump heaters. Controls must be reset each time the recovery compressors are shut down. 01/14/22 17:45 - Roland Evans - C0 (common) - HRS.UT.EP-I found a total of 7 signals on the purifier system that had wiring problems. I found 5 analog input channels wired incorrectly TP73224H, PT73262, TP73124H, TP73112, TP73212. They were wired for rack power instead of field power. I found 2 analog input channels TP73224H, TP73212 that were occupied by incorrect transmitters. I tested each channel bacK to EPICS. They are all correct. I also move the LN2 liquid level back to it's original location on the same card. it seems with all of the miswiring on this one card, it caused the level to read incorrectly. These analog input cards share resources so a miswiring can cause other channels to read oddly or not work at all. "01/14/22 17:18 - Dayne Robinson - C0 (common) - HRS.UT.SW-Corrected Field Wiring for Purifier 1 Nitrogen Boiler Liquid Level Did a download of updated C-UTIL-PLC Code. "01/14/22 16:05 - Dayne Robinson - C0 (common) - HRS.UT.HD-Swapped Analog Input Cards on Utility PLC while Troubleshooting Purifier Signals. Corrected Field Wiring"

title: Owl shift HRS-log
text: "01/15/22 04:30 - Tim DeGraff - C1 - HRS.4K.00-Repaired Leak on C1-LT22195A. - Level probe is entirely solid; hard G10 sleeve with shielding disks. - Attempted to remove with crane. Found Probe is longer than from 4k flange to bottom of crane bridge. - Since crane was not possible, used pole with hook to carefully lift level probe out of subcooler. - Found CF gasket not completely engaged. No other issues found other than minimal dirt. - Cleaned and reinstalled level probe with new CF gasket. - Passed leak check with background of 3.0e-5. - Purged level probe connection port while removing using GHe bottle regulated to 2psi supplying purge gas at test port of PT22195." 01/15/22 04:15 - Tim DeGraff - C1 - HRS.4K.00-4e-4 leak found on He-563 LHe dewar vapor return utube, 4k side, npt connection to bayonet. LHe Dewar needs to be depressurize for repairs. 01/14/22 23:30 - Tim DeGraff - C0 (common) - HRS.00.00-Walkdown complete. Only anomaly: DB-US-VG pressure gauges are not reading back.
